<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-15T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="776" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d776">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115/11583</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-15T17:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 15, 1917, 5 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.35 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5699. Your 4432, February 13 [12]. Foreign Office reply is as
                                follows:</p>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>It is prepared to grant permits for export of German needles
                                    specified in exhibits one to five. “In order, however, to enable
                                    me to give the necessary instructions for the issue of the
                                    permit, I have the honour to enquire whether I could be supplied
                                    with a list setting forth clearly the exact quantity and the
                                    value of smooth needles for which a permit is desired. It has
                                    proved difficult to ascertain from the exhibits whether all
                                    smooth needles shown therein are now awaiting shipment.”</p>
                            </quote>
                            <p>Exhibits are being returned to Department by next bag.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>